thread.title: Atlas 5 rocket launches, sending NASA's robot to Mars

title: Atlas 5 rocket launches, sending NASA's robot to Mars
text:
May 5, 2018 / 11:27 AM / Updated 7 hours ago Atlas 5 rocket launches, sending NASA's robot to Mars Reuters Staff 1 Min Read
(Reuters) - An Atlas 5 rocket soared into space early on Saturday from Vandenberg Air Force Base in California, carrying NASAâ€™s first robotic lander designed for exploring the deep interior of another planet on its voyage to Mars.
The Mars InSight probe lifted off from the central California coast at 4:05 a.m. PDT, treating early-rising residents across a wide swath of the state to the luminous predawn spectacle of the first U.S. interplanetary spacecraft to be launched over the Pacific. Reporting by Brendan O'Brien; Editing by Janet Lawrence
